social_posts.post_text:
In 2022, I dropped my “Closer” single and also toured with G Soul.  For 2023, I’d like to manifest a Asia tour and festival shows. 

I am grateful for every listener and stream.  And all the friends, family, artists, and creatives that have supported me along this journey.

Here’s a piano snippet to a ballad that’s been sitting in my pocket for almost 2 years now.  It’s called, “Love & War.” It’s all done being written and I’ve laid down the background vocals/harmonies, but haven’t perfected the lead lines yet.  Right now, it just needs to make it to the right producer that can bring it to life. 🤞🏼 C’mon, world wide web!

“I want you to start dancing again.” - My doctor.

It’s been over a year since I last practiced.  Starting easy with some tops.  Will add more energy and hips next session.  Blessed to have this community.  #doctorsorders
Picking myself back up.  I also pick up coins, friends, and family in the same fashion.

FYMFI, y’all! “Swing My Way” w/ @chachamalone just crossed 3.5 million @spotify streams, 650k @youtube plays, 500k @applemusic streams.  Can y’all tell @colorsxstudios or @nprmusic that a Cambodian artist signed to a Korean label that lives in America would love to perform for them?  #haveyoueverlovedacambodian
#heresyourchance #squeekywheelgetsthegrease 
#ifnojustlikemypostandvalidatemepls

Thank you @tedparkboi for having me.  I got to try some songs I’ve never done live before and had a great time.  Shout out to @chachamalone for spinning, @hype.pins for running sound and merch, @hellocindeee & @jeannasbeautybook for hair and making me look like I didn’t sleep like crap, and @samfuphoto and @paulkaidoasyn for the photos.  Also, @shy.mov @sangstaa @jarvdee killed it too!
OC show 06/25 with some legends.  Tix avail.  See you soon.

OC was the old stomping grounds. 
Used to study music at Fullerton while living in Anaheim & LBC.  Roll thru as music comes geographically full circle for me. 

Early bird discounted tickets avail in @myxglobal bio link.  Shout out @thefeelgoodcollective @rnbbrand

Disclaimer:  I don’t look this awesome anymore..
I look awesomer.

My handsome, resilient, and smart nephew.  I’m beyond proud of you for graduating high school with all you’ve traversed and overcome.  With this new chapter, I have some words of wisdom to carry you into your mid 20’s.

You will be remembered for what you spend your time doing.

Knowledge is expensive because it gives you truth, advantage, and power.

Everyone in life has a price to pay.  The price goes up the longer you wait. 

Take time to learn and develop strong integrity, grit, boundaries, discipline, accountability, and resourcefulness. 

Start your morning with greatday.com to maintain a healthy mentality.

Youtube Jim Rohn’s talks, “How to Take Charge of Your Life” and “How to Have the Best Year Ever.” Watch it on 1.5x speed.  These 4 hours will set you up with the right mindset.

Embrace the good people who make you feel good, support you, and let you know when you’re wrong.  If it ain’t adding, it’s subtracting.

You’re a POC in America.  Expect to work twice as hard to yield the same results, and consequences for mess ups to be twice as severe.  Navigate carefully.

What sometimes can feel like the end of the world is the beginning of a new one.

Not everything will work out the way you want.  You can calibrate your aim, or change the target.  Every rejection is redirection. 

What you want is on the other side of fear.  Be virtuous, wise, and bold.

Starting anything is easy.  Finishing is hard.  Plan, execute, and see it through.

You represent yourself, our family, our community, and Khmer people.  You have the power and capability to make us all proud and move Khmer people forward.

Have compassion for yourself and others.  If you find yourself harboring anger and resentment that it means you’re a prisoner to it.  Forgiving doesn’t mean you have to forget or allow someone in your life.

Don’t be afraid to come to me for guidance or an ear to listen.  If I ever apply pressure on you, know that it comes from a well-meaning place.  I’m just trying to offer the guidance I wish I had when I was your age.  Your ship has only docked and is ready to set sail in any heading you decide.  Hats off to you for the first of many milestone achievements.

Another year around the sun and I’m reminded of how loved I am. 

With this, I’ve been thinking about all the things I’ve learned thus far, and all the things I need to unlearn.

My February VO2 Max was 31.2.  Today, it’s 38.9! 💪🏽 New Year’s Goal of 44.9, which is considered excellent cardiovascular health. 

VO2 Max is a measurement of how efficiently your body uses oxygen.  The higher the better.  An increase of as little as 3.5 points has shown to reduce chances of cardiovascular disease by 25%.

We should all take our health seriously.  I’ve reduced stress levels, eating more “Blue Zones” meals, aiming for 150 mins of exercise per week, yoga, meditation (Calm app), no alcohol, no caffeine, no smoking, no BS from nobody.

I’d love to do a set at @sabaideefest next summer.  I’m a humble man, don’t ask for much, and have always repped my crew, community, and people thru dance and music.  This festival is a long overdue unifying event for Southeast Asian artists, so there’s much to celebrate.  Can y’all go tag me in @sabaideefest’s comments if y’all think I would be a good fit?
🙏🏼🇰🇭🙏🏼
Where ever you go, there you are.  AOM FOREVER.  BTC FOREVER.
